# Digero Environment Variables
# Copy this file to .env.local and fill in your values

# =============================================================================
# CLERK AUTHENTICATION
# =============================================================================

# Clerk Publishable Key (from Clerk Dashboard > API Keys)
# Required for client-side authentication
EXPO_PUBLIC_CLERK_PUBLISHABLE_KEY=pk_test_your-publishable-key-here

# =============================================================================
# CONVEX BACKEND
# =============================================================================

# Convex Deployment URL (from Convex Dashboard)
EXPO_PUBLIC_CONVEX_URL=https://your-deployment.convex.cloud

# =============================================================================
# REVENUECAT SUBSCRIPTION
# =============================================================================

# RevenueCat Public API Key (from RevenueCat Dashboard > Project > API Keys)
# Required for client-side SDK initialization (iOS key)
EXPO_PUBLIC_REVENUECAT_API_KEY=appl_your_api_key_here

# =============================================================================
# CONVEX ENVIRONMENT VARIABLES (set via npx convex env set)
# =============================================================================
# The following must be set in Convex environment:
#
# CLERK_WEBHOOK_SECRET - Clerk webhook signing secret
# REVENUECAT_WEBHOOK_SECRET - RevenueCat webhook authorization header
# GEMINI_API_KEY - Google Gemini API key for AI recipe extraction
# YOUTUBE_API_KEY - YouTube Data API v3 key for video/channel data
# SPEECHMATICS_API_KEY - Speechmatics Flow API key for voice assistant
# INSTACART_API_KEY - Instacart Developer Platform API key for shopping

# =============================================================================
# YOUTUBE DATA API SETUP
# =============================================================================
# To get a YouTube API key:
#
# 1. Go to Google Cloud Console: https://console.cloud.google.com/
# 2. Create a new project or select an existing one
# 3. Enable the YouTube Data API v3:
#    - Go to: APIs & Services > Enable APIs and services
#    - Search for "YouTube Data API v3"
#    - Click Enable
# 4. Create credentials:
#    - Go to: APIs & Services > Credentials
#    - Click "Create Credentials" > "API Key"
#    - Copy the API key
# 5. Set in Convex:
#    npx convex env set YOUTUBE_API_KEY your_api_key_here
#
# QUOTA LIMITS:
# - Default: 10,000 units per day
# - videos.list: 1 unit per call
# - channels.list: 1 unit per call
# - search.list: 100 units per call
# - captions.list: 50 units per call
#
# The app implements caching to conserve quota.

# =============================================================================
# CLERK DASHBOARD CONFIGURATION REQUIRED
# =============================================================================
# The following must be configured in the Clerk Dashboard:
#
# 1. EMAIL/PASSWORD AUTHENTICATION
#    - Go to: Configure > Email, phone, username
#    - Enable: Email address (as identifier)
#    - Enable: Password (as authentication factor)
#
# 2. APPLE SIGN-IN
#    - Go to: Configure > Social connections
#    - Enable: Apple
#    - Configure: Add your Apple Services ID and Apple Key ID
#    - Note: Requires Apple Developer account ($99/year)
#
# 3. GOOGLE SIGN-IN
#    - Go to: Configure > Social connections
#    - Enable: Google
#    - Configure: Add your Google OAuth Client ID and Secret
#    - Note: Configure in Google Cloud Console first
#
# 4. WEBHOOK (for Convex sync)
#    - Go to: Configure > Webhooks
#    - Add endpoint: https://your-convex-deployment.convex.site/clerk-webhook
#    - Select events: user.created, user.updated, user.deleted
#    - Copy the signing secret to Convex environment variables

# =============================================================================
# REVENUECAT DASHBOARD CONFIGURATION REQUIRED
# =============================================================================
# The following must be configured in the RevenueCat Dashboard:
#
# 1. CREATE PROJECT
#    - Go to: Projects > Create new project
#    - Name: Digero
#
# 2. ADD iOS APP
#    - Go to: Apps > New > iOS
#    - Bundle ID: com.digero.app (match your app.config.ts)
#    - App Store Connect API Key: Configure for server-side receipt validation
#
# 3. CREATE PRODUCTS
#    - digero_premium_monthly ($4.99/month)
#    - digero_premium_annual ($39.99/year, 7-day trial)
#    - digero_premium_lifetime (one-time purchase)
#
# 4. CREATE ENTITLEMENT
#    - Name: premium
#    - Add all three products to this entitlement
#
# 5. CREATE OFFERING
#    - Identifier: default
#    - Add all three products as packages
#
# 6. CONFIGURE WEBHOOK
#    - Go to: Project Settings > Integrations > Webhooks
#    - Add endpoint: https://your-convex-deployment.convex.site/webhooks/revenuecat
#    - Authorization header: Your webhook secret
#    - Copy the authorization header value to Convex REVENUECAT_WEBHOOK_SECRET
